        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Well getting there is easy.  IVU will getcha there without issues if you are careful.  Getting him alone is the key.  You must use the charm/fd trick to get him alone at 49.  Basically charm one, hope it sticks.  Once it does let him get vaporized, then FD.  If it fails you need to use HS and try again.  If it fails yet again, you may be able to make it to zone, due to funky pathing, without dying but its doubtful.  If it works /q out and come back and rinse/repeat till hes alone or if you are feeling frisky, with just one frog.  You DO NOT want them remembering you and coming back after a FD, you will die for sure then, so just /q out.  You have plenty of time before repops, and you wanna split it up anyway if you plan on holding it.  Once you got him .. its not tooooo hard.</P><P> As everyone else here has said, you MUST stop him from casting.  He will waste your pet in no time, no matter how much you pact, if you let him cast.  Key is dropping him as fast as possible.  This is also why I /q out so I can be absolutely FM when I go for the kill.  Heres how I did it.</P><P>fresh diamondskin<BR>buff pet (key for dps and possible interrupts)<BR>sic pet on magus<BR>Bond of Death<BR>cast ST ... trust me hes nuking your pet at this point :p<BR>VoS (dont bother with IB or anything, if hes alive that long you will be dead)<BR>Drain Soul till dead<BR>He will turn on you as some point but hopefully the pet, BoD, VoS and the drain souls will have taken him low enough to channel the last darin or 2.  If not you can always FD until pets at a sliver or dies, give you a bit more breathing room.</P><P> Others might have a better way of doing it, but this is how I managed.  I am not familiar with the velious/luclin spells, as I dont play all that much anymore.  I wouldnt think the slow would help much tho.  His melee is not the issue and slow wont affect his cast times.</P><P><BR><p><font face="Arial" color="#ff9900" font size="2"><palign="center"><strong>Retrievil Hesevil<br><BR>'If you have a problem, if no one else can help, and if you can<BR>find him, maybe you can hire ... The Evil One.'<br><BR>-Tallon Zek -</p><a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
