        &nbsp;<a href="post.asp?method=ReplyQuote&amp;REPLY_ID=35314&amp;TOPIC_ID=4476&amp;FORUM_ID=2&amp;CAT_ID=1&amp;Forum_Title=General+Discussions&amp;Topic_Title=Is+the+Ghoul+Arch+Magus+doable+solo+at+level+49%3F&amp;M="><img src="icon_reply_topic.gif" height="15" width="15" alt="Reply with Quote" border="0" align="absmiddle" hspace="6"></a>

        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         I held this camp at 47, but could not take the Arch magus.  His nuke hits for around 500...  I just dinged 49 myself, and might make another go at it, if I can get my 49 research spells... Think outside the box a little on this one too.  Often the hand, and the lord are camped, which means everything around there is being pulled, so fear is actually an option.  If that's the case, I would just take him as low as you can before you have to fear, and then use it.  Once he's feared nuke the heck out of him, and he probably won't make it far enough to get any adds.  My strat would be as follows...  </P><P>open with slow, and send pet.  You can't pull him because he nukes as soon as you aggro him.  This way you take the first nuke, but pet will take the second.  Otherwise you will get nuked twice, and die before pet has a chance to take aggro, because unless you have buffs, two full dmg nukes will earn you low health aggro, and you're done for.  I know I only have about 1000hp at 49.  Pet should be able to take two nukes before you have to fear, perhaps 3 with slow on.  Trying to heal pet would be a waste of time, and so would ST in my opinion.  Time better spent doing dmg.  You won't beat him to the punch with ST, unless you start casting it before he does, and your heal will not keep up to a mob nuking for 500 dmg a shot.  </P><P>Anyway, after you take the first nuke for half your life, pet will take aggro, and take the second nuke, then you snare with cascading darkness, and dot with BOD.  Then watch pet health, and nuke the crap out of him with undead nukes, or lifetaps if you need to, trying to take aggro back.  By the time you get aggro back pet has probably taken a couple nukes, and getting low on health, but you're full health again, and ready to take another nuke for your pet, and you've done significant dmg to the magus by now also.  So, by the time you and your pet have both taken two nukes, you have done enough dmg to fear.  Panic the dead should be easy to get off with a slowed mob beating on you.  Once he's feared another nuke or two ought to finish him off.  </P><P>This is just my opinion from my experience, but I personally don't think you have the time to wait for dots to work on this guy.  You have to kill him as fast as possible, his dps is just too high.  You can try aggroing with slow, and chain casting ST if you want, and maybe pet can take him out, but if you try to get other spells off like snare, BOD, and heal pet I'd be willing to bet you'll die, because he basically just chain nukes, and the time it takes you to cast those spells will be all the time he needs to kill either you or your pet, depending on who's got aggro, and if your pet goes down you might as well FD.</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
